Reasoning: The paper deals with online scheduling of requests with deadlines, which is a classic problem in computer science. The focus on minimizing the maximum delay factor suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of competitive analysis and the consideration of both unicast and broadcast models suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), algorithms (cs.AL), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
